<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-492-670  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 492 670.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  May 21 1990 v7 n21 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>British Telecom cuts 5,000 jobs in restructuring effort.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Messmer, Ellen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>British Telecommunications PLC is laying off 5,000 middle managersby Apr 1991 and is expected to lay off between 25,000 and 30,000additional workers during the 1990s as part of a restructuringplan that the telephone company hopes will make it more efficient.andO;British Telecom is dismantling its 27-district system in favor ofa nine-region Personal Communications Division to handleresidential customers and a six-region Business CommunicationsDivision to handle commercial customers.andP;  The restructuring isexpected to create a more efficient system of communications thatwill provide a single point of contact for U.S.-based globalcustomers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (layoffs).andO;Topic:     LayoffTelephone CompaniesStrategic PlanningReorganization.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>